solutions.content:
This question uses DFS or flood fill algorithm to traverse the grid.
Step 1: Find the starting point in the given grid
Step 2: Make a **visited matrix** and **initialize it to 0** also make an **answer variable** and **initialize it to 0** as well
Step 3: Make a call to the DFS function 
____________DFS function accepts  following parameters:-
__________GRID , ROW INDEX(starting) , COLUMN INDEX(starting), ans, visited 



**Inside DFS function:**

Step 1: Check the **validity of row and column** also **check if it is non movable block** and **check for visited**. If any of the conditions are met we just return
Step 2: Check if the position we are current on is the ending position or not
--->**if yes,**  then traverse the **entire visited matrix** , if any block is not visited just return.
--->**else**, if every block is visited** increment the ans by  1 and return**
 Step 3: If it is **not the final position** then **mark the visited as 1**  and perform DFS on the neighbouring cells 
 -->i,e.** row+1, col  || row-1, col || row, col+1 || row, col-1**

 After  all the DFS calls are completed just return the ans from the main function

```

class Solution {
public:
void solve(vector<vector<int>>&grid,int row,int col,int &ans,vector<vector<int>>vis){
//// CHECK FOR ALL THE INVALID CASES
if(row<0 || row>=grid.size() || col<0 || col>=grid[0].size() || vis[row][col]==1 || grid[row][col]==-1){
return;
